oreground-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"section\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"The Anatomy of Gamepad Buttons\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Every button press on a controller relies on a simple mechanical-to-electrical connection. Beneath the plastic caps of your face buttons and D-pad sits a flexible silicon membrane embedded with conductive carbon pills. When you press a button, this silicon pad compresses, causing the carbon pill to bridge the copper tracks on the circuit board, which completes the electrical circuit.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"Over millions of press cycles, the conductive carbon wears down and the silicon membrane loses its elasticity. This degradation leads to mushy buttons, double presses, or complete button registration failure, which you can easily diagnose using our telemetry indicators.\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"Accessing the Online Button Tester\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"To test your controller button responsiveness, open our online gamepad tester in your web browser. This interface communicates directly with the browser Gamepad API to parse raw hardware input values.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"For security reasons, your browser will not share your controller signals until you interact with the page. Simply connect your controller and press any button to wake the interface. The tool will instantly display the controller profile and layout map.\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"2\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"Analyzing Face Buttons and D-Pad\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"With the page active, press your controller face buttons one at a time. The tester will highlight each pressed button on the display and report its activation value. For standard binary buttons, this value should immediately jump from 0.00 to 1.00.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"Test your D-pad by pressing each direction individually. If you notice that you have to press a button unusually hard to register a value of 1.00, your conductive pads are beginning to fail. For advanced diagnostic guides, check our \",[\"$\",\"$L3\",\"233\",{\"href\":\"/blog/how-to-use-gamepad-tester\",\"className\":\"text-primary hover:underline font-semibold\",\"children\":\"tutorial on how to use an online gamepad tester\"}],\".\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"3\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"Diagnosing Sticky Buttons and Contact Failure\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Sticky buttons are usually caused by soda spills, sweat, or dust accumulating around the plastic housing. This residue creates friction, preventing the button from returning to its default resting state.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"If the button indicator stays highlighted in our tester log even after you release the physical button, you have a sticky button issue. In most cases, you can clean these contacts by applying a few drops of 99% isopropyl alcohol around the seams, or by following our guide on fixing a gamepad button not working.\"]}]],[\"$\",\"figure\",null,{\"className\":\"my-4 space-y-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"relative aspect-[2.4/1] w-full rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-border\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L4\",null,{\"src\":\"/diagnostic-cleaning.png\",\"alt\":\"Cleaning mechanical button contacts under casing\",\"fill\":true,\"sizes\":\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 672px\",\"className\":\"object-cover\"}]}],[\"$\",\"figcaption\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[10px] text-foreground-muted text-center italic\",\"children\":\"Clean key contacts using 99% isopropyl alcohol\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"4\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"Verifying Bumpers, Triggers, and Menu Buttons\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Finally, test your bumpers, menu buttons, and triggers. Unlike standard face buttons, analog triggers measure pressure sensitivity, outputting values smoothly between 0.00 and 1.00.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"If your triggers register inputs unevenly, refer to our trigger testing guide. If you encounter connection issues during testing, check our \",[\"$\",\"$L3\",\"140\",{\"href\":\"/blog/controller-not-connecting-pc\",\"className\":\"text-primary hover:underline font-semibold\",\"children\":\"guide on fixing controllers not connecting to PC\"}],\", or return to our homepage to test your stick drift coordinates.\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"5\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"Checking Switch Actuation Travel and Latency\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Tactile switch travel determines how quickly an electrical connection is completed after physical compression. Mechanical switches feature shorter travel distances than silicone dome buttons.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"Shorter travel curves yield significantly lower input latency. You can measure and compare responsiveness metrics of mechanical switches vs standard membrane buttons on our real-time testing dashboard.\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"section\",\"6\",{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-extrabold text-foreground border-b border-border/40 pb-2\",\"children\":\"How to Repair Mushy Silicone Membranes\"}],[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Mushy feedback is caused by structural tears in the silicone web dome. When the dome splits, it can no longer push the plastic keycap back up to its original height.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"To repair this, you will need to open the controller casing and replace the silicone button pads with a new manufacturer replacement set, restoring standard spring return forces.\"]}]],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-10 p-5 bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-xl flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-start sm:items-center\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex-1 space-y-1\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-bold text-primary block\",\"children\":\"Free Tool\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed\",\"children\":\"Use our free Gamepad Tester to verify stick drift, check axis coordinates, run circularity tests, and calibrate deadzones — no download required.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex gap-2 shrink-0\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white rounded-lg text-xs font-bold hover:bg-primary-hover transition\",\"children\":\"Test Your Controller\"}],[\"$\",\"$L3\",null,{\"href\":\"/calibration\",\"className\":\"px-4 py-2 bg-background border border-border text-foreground text-xs font-bold rounded-lg hover:bg-surface transition\",\"children\":\"Calibration Tool\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-border/60 flex flex-wrap gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"Testing\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"Testing\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Buttons\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"Buttons\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"D-Pad\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"D-Pad\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Diagnostics\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"Diagnostics\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Xbox\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"Xbox\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"PlayStation\",{\"className\":\"bg-background border border-border/80 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs text-foreground-muted\",\"children\":[\"#\",\"PlayStation\"]}]]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface/50 border border-border/50 rounded-xl p-4 mt-6 text-xs text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground block mb-1\",\"children\":\"Hardware Modification Disclaimer:\"}],\"DIY diagnostic checkups and repairs carry safety risks. Ensure all power supplies are unplugged and follow safety procedures. GamepadTester.live is not liable for components damaged during disassembly or repair attempts.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"lg:col-span-1 space-y-6\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-5 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[10px] font-bold font-display text-primary uppercase tracking-widest block mb-3\",\"children\":\"Written By\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"img\",null,{\"src\":\"/alex-mercer.jpg\",\"alt\":\"Alex Mercer portrait\",\"className\":\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full object-cover border border-border\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\